                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/864½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-24T18:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 25—12:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. President Zayas has just informed me that, assuming the loan is approved, he
                    desires service of Governor Harding<note n="55" xml:id="d867fn55">W. P. G.
                        Harding, Governor of the Federal Reserve Board.</note> in connection with
                    the forthcoming audit and upon terms and conditions mentioned by me. He hopes
                    that he may report on November 1st, or as soon thereafter as practicable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
